-- German Cabinet Approves Minister Roesler's Bill to Reduce Drug Spending
-- Brian Parkin
-- 2010-06-29T09:05:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/german-cabinet-approves-minister-roesler-s-bill-to-reduce-drug-spending.html

          
          
             Chancellor Angela Merkel’s Cabinet
backed a bill to cut drug spending by about 1.7 billion euros
with new rules that break pharmaceutical companies’ hold on
prices.  
 The decision was made by ministers meeting in Berlin today,
the government said. The bill will now to parliament for
approval.  
